shortDescription: Love, What is it good for. Not the two for one deal at Karbies thats for sure. I mean seriously what is up with that deal, they say bring someone you love and I brought a mirror. Can't they understand that the Great Duncan Fisher only has one love and thats chicken wings served in super sauce. Oh, this.. This was just a mistake of a mission. Obviously a trap... .
longDescription: Duncan amazes me, His blood alcohol level has to be near flammable, How does he keep going?

contractObjectiveList.title: Attempt to Rescue Lord Alexander Madeira

objectiveList.title: Secure the Area to Rescue Alexander
Complete the Data Download in Time

dialogueContent.words: How are we looking, Darius?
Bad news. The APC holding Lord Madeira has already reached the facilty ahead. Whatever we're going to do, we need to do it fast. Our arrival won't stay a secret for long.
I need Alexander by my side if we are going beat my Uncle and win this war. Cut him out of that facility, Commander. We will get that data after he is recovered.
Of course they were close Darius, Why wouldn't they be close? I mean seriously at this point if it wasn't obvious they were luring you in.
I thought if we could lure the vehicles into range we could quickly dispatch them and get the information. And as you know things did not work out as expected.
What is this, Cousin? You're running? Leaving Lord Madeira behind? I thought that you would do anything for each other.
I will take him back from you, Victoria. Personally.
I look forward to it, Kamea. In the interim, know that your dearest friend will languish as I languished in Lord Karosas's dungeons. I will make him suffer in your stead.
I know what I'm abandoning him to, Victoria—as does he. Alexander is more courageous than either of us, and if you hurt him, I will kill you myself. I swear that on my father's name.
All targets eliminated. Sit tight, and I can collect you from where you are at right now.
What is this, cousin? You're running? Leaving Lord Madeira behind? I thought that you would do anything for each other.
I will take him back from you, Victoria. Personally.
I look forward to it, Kamea. In the interim, know that your dearest friend will languish as I languished in Lord Karosas's dungeons. I will make him suffer in your stead.
I know what I'm abandoning him to, Victoria—as does he. Alexander is more courageous than either of us, and if you hurt him, I will kill you myself. I swear that on my father's name.
New sensor contacts! I've got hostile units converging on your location!
Damn you, Victoria! Taking hostages is a coward's move. If you wanted to fight me, you should've come yourself!
When I send you to hell, be sure to tell Lord Karosas that.
Enough of these games, Kamea. Do you want to win little Alex back? Come and find me. We'll be waiting for you… won't we, Lord Madeira?
I'm sorry, Kamea. I evaded capture for as long as I could, but— [loud cracking sound] [muffled cry of pain]
That sound you just heard was his jaw, Kamea… it was every bit as fragile as I'd thought it would be. Consider this a promise kept from our first reunion.
I'm coming for you, Victoria! Do you hear me?!
Yeah we know, We Know. Capture a loved one to make your enemy come to you. Darius get me another drink, I need it to palet this part. That and the wings just started talking, and they smell bad.
Every fiber of my being is screaming at me to not abandon Lord Madeira. To drop everything and rescue him, as I know he'd rescue me. In leaving him, I betray myself.
It's the right call, and it's what he wanted you to do. For your people.
But Alexander...
He'll live. Have faith in that, and press on. It's the only thing you can do.
Not bad, cousin… but I'm not finished with you yet.
The defenders are elminated. Now secure that base so we can extract Alexander.
Well done, Commander. Farah, do you have a fix on Lord Madeira's exact location?
Working on it, Darius. I just need a minute to -
You won't find your lapdog in that facility, however long you search, Cousin. Little Alex kneels at my feet as we speak.
Get out of here, Kamea! She's using me as bait!
It's true, Kamea. Alexander was excellent bait. And now this war comes to an end.
That's enough for now Lord Maderia, time to see how much your Lady really cares for you.
The Directorate must've learned about Lord Madeira's subdermal transponder and cloned the signal. Keep fighting down there—Sumire and I are working to get a fix on his actual location.
Work quickly, Dr. Murad. This could be our only chance at finding him!
Lady Arano, I've got a fix on Lord Madeira's transponder signal. He's being moved—it looks like they're taking him to the most heavily-reinforced Directorate stronghold on Guldra.
Ms. Meyer! I need you to pick us up in the Leopard. It's the only way we can reach him before it's too late.
That's a negative, Lady Arano. I'm reading dozens of antiaircraft guns and missile turrets around that stronghold. If I tried to fly you in, they'd blow me out of the sky.
Damn it. What are our options?

If you take off at a dead sprint, you might be able to catch them. It'll be pretty dicey, though—I'm seeing a lot of 'Mechs between you and Lord Madeira. And we'll have no time to retrieve the evidence that he gathered.
The evidence can wait, we have to… [tense exhalation] …Damn it.

…That intel is vital to our war effort, and it's nearly in our grasp. I… [long pause] …I cannot risk the future of the Reach for one man. Mr. Oliveira, I need you to give me the coordinates of Lord Madeira's dead drop. Forgive me, Alexander, but your rescue will have to wait.
Roger that, Lady Arano—I'm marking the coordinates on your map now. Commander we show multiple dropships inbound, as soon as you have the Data get out of there!
We're receiving the data now, Lady Arano. Commander, I'm gonna have to ask you to keep one of your 'Mechs near that relay until the upload is finished.
Transmission complete, Lady Arano - we have the package in hand and Sumire is on her way.
That's the last inbound hostile dropship from the landing force we have the window we need to evac.
Destroying my cousin's landing force would show her the costs of her treachery and I am willing pay. However getting that recovering that data is still our priority.
